missionStatement:
THE RELIEF OF SUFFERING AND DISTRESS OF RETIRED AND UNWANTED GREYHOUNDS, INCLUDING, BUT NOT LIMITED TO, THE FOLLOWING:
A) PROVIDING MEDICAL ATTENTION AND TREATMENT FOR THOSE GREYHOUNDS THAT REQUIRE IT;
B) PROVIDING SANCTUARY FOR THOSE GREYHOUNDS WITH MEDICAL OR BEHAVIOURAL ISSUES;
C) ARRANGING CAREFUL AND RESPONSIBLE RE-HOMING OF GREYHOUNDS.
D) THE ADVANCEMENT OF EDUCATION OF THE GENERAL PUBLIC IN MATTERS RELATING TO GREYHOUNDS AND BY THIS MEANS TO PREVENT CRUELTY AND SUFFERING.

Our setting aims to:
	Provide high quality care and education for children below statutory school age;
	Work in partnership with parents to help children to learn and develop;
	Add to the life and well-being of the local community; and
Offer children and their parents a service that promotes equality and values diversity

Cowfold Community Pool is an outdoor heated pool, the  aim of the charity is to
* provide access to for anyone, from any background, age or ability to swimming, for recreation and/to learn a new skill; 
* bring the whole community together;
* promote physical & mental health through water based activities.
The pool was originally built, following the tragic death of three local young men, who drowned. We want to make sure that this tragedy never happens again & encourage people to be water confident.

Suffolk Sight provides practical and realistic solutions to the challenges posed by sight loss for all ages. Our wide range of services help individuals maintain their independence and provides families with advice and direction.
Delivered by professional staff and trained volunteers to anyone living in Suffolk  our services cover:
useful, sound support from our community workers;
helpful, down-to-earth guidance from our technical advisors; 
a sense of community from our social groups and activities
